<div id="about-the-community" class="section-spacer">
    <h2 class="sect-title">About Lakeview</h2>
    <div class="col-grid-2">
        <div>
        <p class="par-lg">Lakeview was established in the 1960â€™s with many of the original homes being built by Engineered Homes Ltd. and comprise of townhouses and bungalows to detached single-family homes. </p>
        <p class="par-lg">Situated at the tail of Crowchild Trail, at the intersection of Glenmore Trail South of Altadore. </p>
        <p class="par-lg">Lakeview homes south of 66th Avenue are part of a smaller, yet well off subdivision called The Lakeview Village, entailing larger estate homes, sitting on Glenmore Park. </p>
        <p class="par-lg">The Calgary School Board has an elementary and junior high school in Lakeview, with Central Memorial being the designated high school in the neighbouring North Glenmore community. </p>
        <p class="par-lg">There is also a public charter school for girls.</p> 
        <p class="par-lg">South of 66th Ave is a smaller development called Lakeview Village, which consists of the more luxurious homes, two storey homes.</p>
        <p class="par-lg">Lakeview homes are located within close proximity of Mount Royal University, making it ideal for University students, and professors. </p>
        <p class="par-lg">Lakeview is also in close proximity to Rocky View Hospital in the off chance a medical emergency occurring.</p>
        </div>
